id16: To condition the hole and tag the top of cement plug #4, a work unaccomplished by the stinger due to hole problems, RR 5b bit was picked up and run in the hole on the same BHA as the previous clean out assembly. The bit was run in to the shoe where the drilling line was slipped and cut. The bit was then run in to 1680m where circulation was started. The trip in continued down to 1740m where resistance was encountered. The bit was washed and reamed from 1740m to 2228m where cement was tagged. A 200be gel pill was swept around the hole before the bit was pulled out of the hole to pick up the sidetrack assembly.
